library(cluster)
library(factoextra)
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
df<- read.csv("/Users/valentinasilva/Downloads/lab-data.csv")
df <- na.omit(df)
# df <- scale(df)

Elbow Method

fviz_nbclust(df, FUN=hcut, method="wss")

#Avg silhouette

fviz_nbclust(df, FUN=hcut, method="silhouette")

Gap Statistic method

gap_stat <- clusGap(df, FUN=hcut, nstart = 25, K.max = 10, B = 50)

fviz_gap_stat(gap_stat)

## K Means Clustering # Elbow Method

set.seed(123)

fviz_nbclust(df, kmeans, method = "wss")

##The elbow point is not that obvious, I’ll increse k.max parameter.

fviz_nbclust(df, kmeans, method = "wss", k.max = 20)

# I’ll pick K=5 as the elbow point, since the slope of the curve seems to be less steep around this value.

Average Silhouette method

fviz_nbclust(df, kmeans, method = "silhouette")

#Gap Statistic method

gap_stat <- clusGap(df, FUN=kmeans, nstart = 25, K.max = 10, B = 50)

fviz_gap_stat(gap_stat)

## Build K-Means model # From previous functions, we get three values for k, which are 5, 2, and 10. Let’s use them to build the models.

k5 <- kmeans(df, centers = 5, nstart = 25)

k2 <- kmeans(df, centers = 2, nstart = 25)

k10 <- kmeans(df, centers = 10, nstart = 25)

Plot the models

p5 <- fviz_cluster(k5, data = df, geom = "point") + ggtitle("k=5")
p2 <- fviz_cluster(k2, data = df, geom = "point") + ggtitle("k=2")
p10 <- fviz_cluster(k10, data = df, geom = "point") + ggtitle("k=10")

library(gridExtra)
